---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Client Terms | FirstLayer Digital">
	<main class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#020617] transition-colors duration-300">
		<!-- Background gradient layers for depth -->
		<div class="fixed inset-0 -z-10">
			<div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[#020617] transition-colors duration-300"></div>
			<div class="absolute top-1/4 right-1/4 w-96 h-96 bg-cyan-900/10 rounded-full blur-3xl transition-colors duration-300"></div>
			<div class="absolute bottom-1/4 left-1/4 w-96 h-96 bg-blue-900/10 rounded-full blur-3xl transition-colors duration-300"></div>
		</div>

		<div class="max-w-4xl 2xl:max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
			<div class="relative">
				<h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-5xl 2xl:text-6xl font-extrabold text-white mb-2 sm:mb-3 leading-tight transition-colors duration-300">
					Client Terms
				</h1>
				<p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-400 mb-8 sm:mb-10 transition-colors duration-300">
					Master Service Agreement | Last updated: January 2026
				</p>

				<div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-headings:text-white prose-headings:font-bold prose-p:text-slate-400 prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-ul:text-slate-400 prose-li:text-slate-400 prose-a:text-cyan-400 prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline prose-strong:text-white">
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						These Client Terms ("Terms") govern the relationship between First Layer Digital LLC ("First Layer Digital," "we," "us," or "our") and our clients ("Client," "you," or "your") regarding the provision of web design, development, and related digital services. By engaging our services, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">1. Services and Deliverables</h2>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						First Layer Digital LLC agrees to provide the services and deliverables as specified in the project proposal, statement of work, or service agreement ("Project Agreement"). All services will be performed in a professional and workmanlike manner, consistent with industry standards.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						Deliverables will be provided in accordance with the timeline and specifications outlined in the Project Agreement. Any changes to scope, timeline, or deliverables must be agreed upon in writing by both parties.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">2. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
					
					<h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-6 sm:mt-8 mb-3 sm:mb-4">2.1 Custom Work Ownership</h3>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						All original custom code, designs, and deliverables created by First Layer Digital LLC specifically for the Client's project shall be the property of First Layer Digital LLC. Upon completion of payment for the project, the Client receives a <strong class="text-white">perpetual, non-exclusive license</strong> to use the deliverables for the Client's own business purposes.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						Deliverables include:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 sm:pl-8 mb-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Custom HTML, CSS, JavaScript code</li>
						<li>Custom PHP/Node.js backend code</li>
						<li>Custom design files and graphics created for this project</li>
						<li>Database structures custom-built for the project</li>
						<li>All implementations and integrations</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						This license grants Client the right to use the Custom Work Product for Client's business purposes, including the right to engage third-party developers to maintain, modify, or extend the Custom Work Product. However, Client may not resell, sublicense, or redistribute the Custom Work Product as a standalone product or service.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-6 sm:mt-8 mb-3 sm:mb-4">2.2 Pre-existing Frameworks and Libraries</h3>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						First Layer Digital LLC may incorporate pre-existing frameworks, libraries, utilities, and templates ("Pre-Existing IP") created by First Layer Digital LLC prior to or independently of this engagement into the project deliverables. These Pre-Existing IP items are the property of First Layer Digital LLC and remain First Layer Digital LLC's property.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						<strong class="text-white">Client's License to Pre-Existing IP:</strong>
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 sm:pl-8 mb-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Client receives a limited, non-exclusive license to use Pre-Existing IP only as incorporated within the deliverables</li>
						<li>Client may not independently license, extract, redistribute, or use Pre-Existing IP for purposes outside the project</li>
						<li>Client may not hire another developer to modify or remove Pre-Existing IP components</li>
						<li>First Layer Digital LLC retains the right to use identical Pre-Existing IP in other client projects</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						Examples of Pre-Existing IP include:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 sm:pl-8 mb-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Reusable code libraries and components</li>
						<li>Configuration templates</li>
						<li>Design system utilities</li>
						<li>API integration patterns</li>
						<li>Deployment scripts and automation tools</li>
						<li>Custom frameworks and boilerplates</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						The Client acknowledges that use of Pre-Existing IP provides significant value and cost savings and agrees to the licensing terms outlined above.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-6 sm:mt-8 mb-3 sm:mb-4">2.3 Client-Provided Content</h3>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						Client retains all ownership rights to content, materials, logos, images, and other assets provided by Client for use in the project. Client grants First Layer Digital LLC a limited, non-exclusive license to use such materials solely for the purpose of performing the services under the Project Agreement.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">3. Payment Terms</h2>
					
					<h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-6 sm:mt-8 mb-3 sm:mb-4">3.1 Payment Schedule</h3>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						Unless otherwise specified in the Project Agreement, payment terms are <strong class="text-white">Net 30</strong> from the date of invoice. Invoices will be issued upon completion of project milestones or as otherwise specified in the Project Agreement.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						For fixed-price projects, a deposit may be required before work begins, with the balance due upon completion and delivery of the final deliverables.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-6 sm:mt-8 mb-3 sm:mb-4">3.2 Late Payment Policy</h3>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						In the event that any invoice is not paid within thirty (30) days of receipt, the Client shall be subject to:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 sm:pl-8 mb-4 space-y-2">
						<li><strong class="text-white">One-time Late Fee: $50.00</strong></li>
						<li><strong class="text-white">Delinquency Charge: 1.5% per month</strong> on the outstanding balance, or the maximum amount permitted by Maryland law, whichever is less</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						Late fees and delinquency charges shall be calculated from the original due date and applied monthly until payment is received in full.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						<strong class="text-white">Service Suspension:</strong> If payment is not received within thirty (30) days of the invoice due date (60+ days from invoice receipt), First Layer Digital LLC reserves the right to suspend all services, including but not limited to website hosting and maintenance, development and design work, support and updates, and access to development environments. All services shall remain suspended until the account is brought current, including payment of all outstanding invoices, late fees, and delinquency charges.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						Client agrees to reimburse First Layer Digital LLC for any costs incurred in collecting overdue amounts, including reasonable attorney's fees.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-6 sm:mt-8 mb-3 sm:mb-4">3.3 Refunds</h3>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						Due to the custom nature of our services, refunds are generally not available once work has commenced. If Client terminates the Project Agreement before completion, Client will be responsible for payment of all work completed up to the termination date, plus any non-refundable expenses incurred.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">4. Post-Launch Support</h2>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						All projects include a <strong class="text-white">60-day post-launch support period</strong> at no additional cost following the project launch date. During this period, First Layer Digital LLC will:
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-3">
						<strong class="text-white">Included in Post-Launch Support:</strong>
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 sm:pl-8 mb-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Identify and fix critical bugs reported by Client</li>
						<li>Address broken links, missing images, or display errors</li>
						<li>Correct spelling/grammar errors in deployed content</li>
						<li>Fix functionality that does not work as specified in the Statement of Work</li>
						<li>Support Client's transition to ongoing website management</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-3">
						<strong class="text-white">Not Included in Post-Launch Support:</strong>
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 sm:pl-8 mb-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Feature enhancements or additions</li>
						<li>Content updates or changes</li>
						<li>Design modifications</li>
						<li>Third-party integrations beyond original scope</li>
						<li>Training or consulting</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						During the 60-day post-launch support period, First Layer Digital LLC shall respond to bug reports within two (2) business days. Critical bugs affecting website functionality shall be prioritized for resolution within 5 business days. After the 60-day period expires, any ongoing support, maintenance, or modifications shall be billed at First Layer Digital LLC's standard hourly rate.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						Support requests must be submitted in writing via email to <a href="mailto:projects@firstlayer.digital">projects@firstlayer.digital</a>.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">5. Client Responsibilities</h2>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						Client agrees to:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 sm:pl-8 mb-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Provide timely feedback and approvals during the project timeline</li>
						<li>Supply all necessary content, materials, and access credentials in a timely manner</li>
						<li>Ensure that all content provided does not infringe upon any third-party rights</li>
						<li>Make timely payments in accordance with the payment terms</li>
						<li>Comply with all applicable laws and regulations related to the project</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						Delays in Client's provision of materials, feedback, or approvals may result in project timeline extensions and may incur additional charges.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">6. Warranties and Disclaimers</h2>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						First Layer Digital LLC warrants that:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 sm:pl-8 mb-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Services will be performed in a professional and workmanlike manner</li>
						<li>Deliverables will substantially conform to the specifications in the Project Agreement</li>
						<li>We have the right to use all materials and intellectual property incorporated into the deliverables</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						EXCEPT AS EXPRESSLY SET FORTH ABOVE, FIRST LAYER DIGITAL LLC MAKES NO WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR NON-INFRINGEMENT.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						First Layer Digital LLC does not guarantee specific results, search engine rankings, or business outcomes. Client acknowledges that website performance and search rankings depend on numerous factors beyond our control.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, FIRST LAYER DIGITAL LLC'S TOTAL LIABILITY FOR ANY CLAIMS ARISING OUT OF OR RELATED TO THESE TERMS OR THE SERVICES PROVIDED SHALL NOT EXCEED THE TOTAL AMOUNT PAID BY CLIENT TO FIRST LAYER DIGITAL LLC UNDER THE APPLICABLE PROJECT AGREEMENT IN THE TWELVE (12) MONTHS PRECEDING THE CLAIM.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						IN NO EVENT SHALL FIRST LAYER DIGITAL LLC BE LIABLE FOR INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING LOST PROFITS, LOST DATA, OR BUSINESS INTERRUPTION, REGARDLESS OF THE THEORY OF LIABILITY.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">8. Confidentiality</h2>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						Both parties agree to maintain the confidentiality of proprietary information disclosed during the course of the project. This includes business plans, technical specifications, trade secrets, and other confidential information.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						Confidentiality obligations do not apply to information that is publicly available, independently developed, or required to be disclosed by law.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">9. Termination</h2>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-4">
						Either party may terminate the Project Agreement:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 sm:pl-8 mb-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Upon written notice if the other party breaches a material term and fails to cure such breach within 30 days</li>
						<li>Immediately if the other party becomes insolvent or files for bankruptcy</li>
						<li>For convenience, with 30 days' written notice (subject to payment for all work completed)</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						Upon termination, Client will pay for all work completed up to the termination date, and First Layer Digital LLC will deliver all completed work product, subject to full payment.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">10. General Provisions</h2>
					
					<h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-6 sm:mt-8 mb-3 sm:mb-4">10.1 Governing Law</h3>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Maryland, United States, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-6 sm:mt-8 mb-3 sm:mb-4">10.2 Entire Agreement</h3>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						These Terms, together with the Project Agreement, constitute the entire agreement between the parties and supersede all prior agreements, understandings, or communications relating to the subject matter.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-6 sm:mt-8 mb-3 sm:mb-4">10.3 Modifications</h3>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						These Terms may be modified by First Layer Digital LLC at any time. Material changes will be communicated to existing clients. Continued use of our services after such modifications constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-6 sm:mt-8 mb-3 sm:mb-4">10.4 Severability</h3>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						If any provision of these Terms is found to be unenforceable or invalid, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-8 sm:mt-10 mb-4 sm:mb-6">11. Contact Information</h2>
					<p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 sm:mb-8">
						For questions about these Terms or to discuss your project, please contact us using the information provided in the footer of this website.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
